name: The State Hotel
description:
The State Hotel features a fitness center, terrace, a restaurant and bar in Seattle. This 4-star hotel offers room service, a 24-hour front desk and free WiFi. The property is 900 feet from the city center and 1.1 miles from Pocket Beach.
Guest rooms in the hotel are equipped with a flat-screen TV.
Popular points of interest near The State Hotel include Space Needle, CenturyLink Field and Washington State Convention Center. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 1.2 miles from the accommodation.

name: Hotel Theodore
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Hotel Theodore! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Hotel Theodore is a nonsmoking hotel located in the heart of downtown Seattle and features a concierge service and fitness center. Rooms offer free WiFi. Washington State Convention Center is 5 minutes' walk away.
A locally influenced honor bar and a gourmet coffee machine are also provided. Guests can also choose to select specialty pillows from the Pillow Bar at the hotel.
The pet-friendly hotel includes dry cleaning and laundry services.
Located next to the lobby, Made Coffee bar is open daily.
Frye Art Museum and Denny Park are 5 minutes’ drive from the hotel. The Space Needle is 0.9 mi away. The Hotel Theodore is located 6 blocks away from Pike Place.

name: Kimpton Hotel Monaco Seattle, an IHG Hotel
description:
Located in Central Seattle, Kimpton Hotel Monaco Seattle features a morning coffee and tea service. All of the contemporary rooms offer free WiFi, a yoga mat, and luxury bath amenities. The Space Needle and Safeco Field are both 0.9 mi away.
A flat-screen cable TV with pay-per-view channels is included in each guest room. All of the air-conditioned rooms feature modern décor and include a mini-bar, a coffee machine, a desk and a seating area. Select rooms provide deep soaking bathtubs and city views.
A 24-hour business center and a 24-hour fitness center are available to guests of Kimpton Hotel Monaco Seattle. Guests can enjoy an afternoon wine reception.
The Washington State Convention Center is 2 minutes’ drive away from Kimpton Hotel Monaco Seattle. Seattle-Tacoma International Airport is 14 mi away.

name: Grand Hyatt Seattle
description:
Less than 10 minutes’ drive from the Space Needle, this Seattle hotel features modern guest rooms with a flat-screen cable TV. A business center and fitness center are both available for guest use.
Floor to ceiling windows are available in each guest room at the Grand Hyatt Seattle. Rooms begin on the 10th floor and offer sweeping city views. A large soaking tub, plush bathrobes, and electronic black-out drapes are also included.
Ruth’s Chris Steakhouse, offering a fine dining experience, is on site at the Seattle Grand Hyatt. Additional dining options include Urbane for American fare and Blue C for fresh sushi. Ruth’s Chris Tasting Room in the Wine Cellar is also available and a Starbucks Coffee is located in the lobby.
The on-site health club features a sauna, steam room, whirlpool, and spa treatments. Guests can also take advantage of the dry cleaning and laundry services offered. A concierge service is provided to assist guests with area attractions and dinner reservations. There is a conference center on site with over 25,000 square feet over meeting space.
The Experience Music Project is 1 miles from the Grand Hyatt. Pike Place Market is 15 minutes’ walk away.

name: Four Seasons Hotel Seattle
description:
This downtown Seattle hotel is 1.2 mi from the Space Needle. This hotel features a full spa, rooftop infinity pool, and outdoor fireplace. Every guest room features Northwest-style decor with wood and stone details.
The Four Seasons Hotel Seattle has a 24-hour business center. Guests can work out in the gym or use the steam room or hot tub. Guests can dine at the Goldfinch Tavern, which features Pacific Northwest cuisine by world renowned chef Ethan Stowell.
Rooms at the Seattle Four Seasons have a marble bathroom with rain showers. Guests can watch the 42-inch flat-screen TV.
The Four Seasons Hotel is within 5 minutes' walk to Pike Place Market. The Seattle Art Museum is 2 minutes' walk to the hotel. The Washington State Convention Center is within 10 minutes' walk from the property and SeaTac International Airport is within 25 minutes' drive.

name: Sheraton Grand Seattle
description:
Featuring an indoor lap pool and state-of-the-art fitness center on the 35th floor, this downtown Seattle hotel is less than 10 minutes’ walk from Pike Place Market. Rooms at the Seattle Sheraton Hotel offer a flat-screen TV.
Over-sized windows with views of downtown Seattle are featured in guest rooms at the Sheraton Seattle Hotel. Coffee-making facilities offering Starbucks coffee are provided.
A gift shop and sundry is on-site and a full service FedEx office business center is offered for guest use. An ATM, shipping supplies, office supplies, shipping services, and computers are provided for guest use.
In Short Order is the Sheraton’s grab-n-go feature, offering sandwiches, salads, and snacks to busy guests.The Sheraton Seattle Hotel also features the urban contemporary French restaurant, Loulay Kitchen & Bar. Fountain Wine Bar and Lounge offers evening cocktails.
The Seattle Monorail's Westlake Station and the Washington State Convention Center are less than 5 minutes’ walk from the hotel. CenturyLink Field, home of the Seattle Seahawks and Seattle Sounders FC, is less than 10 minutes’ drive away.

userReviews.title: A not so Grand Experience
userReviews.positive: Good location, close to all amenities or within easy travelling distance, close to monorail and Metro lines, restaurants and bars as well as Pike Place Market. The bed was very big and comfortable and the room had a good, quiet airconditioning unit and good choice of TV channels.
userReviews.negative: The area is full of homeless people who seem to all have an array of mental health and drug/alcohol issues, which is to be expected in any downtown area but I've never seen it this bad and I've been to London, England, where homelessness is rampant. Also, it seems nobody knows he city. We had a taxi driver asking us directions to a venue we were visiting (I'm pretty sure it's their job to know all areas of the city). We also asked a cop for a directions and he was just as useless. The hotel staff did not mention anything about the pool being closed for maintenance, not even at check-in. We found out ourselves, unfortunately, which isn't very good considering I booked this hotel solely for the pool. There's no vending machines in the hotel. It has a Starbucks that closed around 5pm and the area doesn't seem to have a nearby convenience. It's quite sad really because the hotel is absolutely lush with big rooms and eloquently set-up to cater to all tastes.

name: Hilton Motif Seattle
description:
The Hilton Motif Seattle overlooks the city center streets of Seattle, featuring scenic views of Seattle and the Olympic Mountains, Guests here can enjoy the on-site restaurant and bar,
Each room and suite at Hilton Motif Seattle: comes with NEST Bath & Body products, a JBL Bluetooth alarm clock, and a gourmet coffee machine. Additional amenities include a flat-screen TV with premium channels, a refrigerator and bathrobes.
A modern and fully equipped business center and meeting facilities are available on site. A fitness center, a 24-hour front desk are also offered. American cuisine with a Northwest flair and evening cocktails are served at the Frolik Kitchen + Cocktails, which features a spacious outdoor patio. Games and a relaxing seating area can also be found at the restaurant.
The Seattle Art Museum is less than 10 minutes’ walk from the hotel. The Washington State Convention Center is 5 minutes’ walk away and the Ferry Terminal is just 0.9 mi from Hilton Motif Seattle.

userReviews.title: An excellent choice for a couple of days stopover in Seattle!
userReviews.positive:
Check-in: A fantastic first impression. We'd had quite the day and arriving here finished it with a check-in experience beyond expectation. We were offered complimentary wine and beer on arrival (which we really needed!). Plus you can have snacks and sodas at any time during your visit. The person at the desk was friendly, helpful and efficient, making the check-in process easy and pleasant.
Location: A few minutes' walk to Pike Place Market and the waterfront.
Room: Comfortable and clean. It was exactly as described. Comfortable bed and extra pillows. Reasonably quiet. One thing I loved (that many hotels do not have) was the bathroom vanity has plenty of bench space to put your things and the lighting was also adequate enough to apply make-up
Restaurant and Bar: We ate dinner one night and breakfast here. Our meals were nice and the servers were friendly and interested in having a bit of a chat. The room had a comfortable ambience and it was reasonably busy. There is an English pub underneath the hotel which was also pretty good.
Every staff member that we interacted with was friendly and helpful throughout the stay.
userReviews.room: Queen Room with Two Queen Beds

name: The Inn at Virginia Mason
description:
Ideally located for patients and travelers, The Inn at Virginia Mason is located in a residential neighborhood of Seattle and is located next to Virginia Mason Medical Center. Just steps from the city center, this hotel offers a rooftop garden with stunning views of the city. Pike Place Market is less than 1.2 mi away, while the Washington State Convention Center is 2,450 feet from the hotel.
The Inn at Virginia Mason is a completely smoke free hotel with non air-conditioned guestrooms. After a busy day exploring Seattle, guests can relax and watch cable TV on their in-room flat-screen TV. A coffee maker, hairdryer, and ironing facilities are also included in each room.
Additional services at the hotel include a business center with fax, copy, and printing. Self-parking is available nearby. The property can arrange transportation to and from the cruise ship terminals at an additional cost.
The Inn at Virginia Mason is within 10 minutes' drive of CenturyLink Field, Safeco Field, and WaMu Theater. SeaTac International Airport is 25 minutes' drive from the hotel.

name: Renu Seattle-Cute, Cozy and Historical
description:
Offering city views and free WiFi, Renu Seattle-Cute, Cozy and Historical has accommodations ideally set in the center of Seattle, within a short distance of Seattle Center Monorail, Columbia Center and Washington State Convention Center.
The accommodations come with a flat-screen TV and a private bathroom with shower, bath and free toiletries, while the kitchen has a fridge, an oven and a microwave. A stovetop and toaster are also offered, as well as an electric tea pot.
Popular points of interest near the condo hotel include Seattle Great Wheel, Seattle Aquarium and King Street Station. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base, 2.5 miles from Renu Seattle-Cute, Cozy and Historical, and the property offers a paid airport shuttle service.

userReviews.negative:
I could not access the room so had to rent a different hotel room the first night.
The instructions were incorrect. There was a video indicating the building's front door could be opened by a code but it couldn't. a key was needed. I had to download an app to open the room door but the app did not work. WiFi was required to use the app and I was not informed of that. I was not provided with the building's wifi code until half way through the second day. I needed the wifi code to use the app to open the room door so I had not access to the room the first rental day. It took 2 days and 3 trips to the building to gain access. This was a total nightmare! 
I would like a full refund as I wasted most of my vacation trying to gain access to the room.

userReviews.title: Great location, reasonable pricing and large space.
userReviews.positive:
Great open space and all the amenities you would expect from an apartment. Checking in seemed a little overwhelming at first due to the lengthy emails received, however, it makes perfect sense once you arrive and ensures that you do not need to contact the owners again as the information is already provided. Location is great, being very central to all the tourist hotspots, although, as this is the USA, it still means a 10-15 min walk to each place as a minimum. Very few bars within the vicinity, however, Capitol Hill is only a 10 min walk away which is without doubt the best place to experience the Seattle nightlife (providing you’re not prejudice).  Be warned however that the apartment is at the top of a VERY steep hill but considering all of Seattle is like this, it’s no surprise! 
The apartment uses a phone app to gain access to the property which means you never have to worry about keys and is very simple and effective to use. It is a little worn around the edges and by no means perfect but considering the prices in Seattle, this is a reasonable price for the space you’re getting. 
My brother stated the double bed was very comfy, however I’m sorry to say that the sofa bed needs updating as not good at all. Would have liked a couple of duvets or comforters available as the room dropped in temperature in the evening and we were limited in what we were provided. Overall a good experience and providing you’re not expecting the Ritz, it does the job. 
It’s a shame that Seattle has a big issue in homelessness and drug use, however this was definitely reduced in the area we were based, making it feel less intimidating and unsafe to walk at night compared to other areas.
userReviews.negative: Limited bedding and the sofa bed. A little most attention to detail on the cheating would be a benefit but didn’t affect our stay.

userReviews.title: AVOID! Extremely poor value for money and lacking basic cleanliness standards.
userReviews.positive: This place's only saving grace was the relatively fully-loaded kitchen.
userReviews.negative: AVOID! This place does not meet basic comfort and cleanliness standards for $300/night accommodations in this part of the world. I counted at least eight issues, ranked in order of egregiousness: 1) Bathroom sink was clogged and full of dirty water; reported immediately but was ever fixed during our 4-night stay. 2) Bed and linens smelled funny (bodily fluids?). 3) Overwhelmingly strong smell of cleaning products and fragrance upon entry. 4) Medicine cabinet in bathroom full of loose, cut hair. 5) Window sills and curtains are dusty and grimy. 6) All the furniture is basically broken. 7) Freezer door was completely wide open and warm inside upon entry. 8) Unnecessarily complicated check-in procedure completely reliant on technology/smartphones.

That means: Fully disclose all the Fees and charges that are in the Price listed for the stay, Do Not Hide those Fees in the small print elsewhere and Do Not Only Show a Price without the Fees, that is what Bait and Switch Is !

userReviews.title: Garbage, wasted hours trying to get checked in, thanks to Secure Stay booking "system."
userReviews.negative: This was the worst hotel experience I ever had.  It was a same-day booking, when my flight out of Seattle was canceled and I needed a place to say - everything else was booked.  This property uses a "service" called SecureStay to obtain information from the guest and provide a virtual key.  It took literally two hours to get checked in, via text messages and links on my cel phone, and even after checking in they failed to send the virtual key they were supposed to send...another hour to find out that the door to the room was unlocked and no virtual key was necessary, despite all their texts and emails to the contrary.  No air conditioning - no wonder this was the only property with a vacancy in the entire city.  Completely frustrating experience.  If there's a way to find out which properties use "Secure Stay," I'd love to know,...I will never, ever book such a property again, I'd rather sleep on the floor at the airport.

name: The Alexis Royal Sonesta Hotel Seattle
description:
Located in the city center of Seattle, The Alexis Royal Sonesta Hotel Seattle is 5 minutes' walk from the waterfront and the Seattle Ferry Terminal. Rooms offer a flat-screen cable TV. The hotel is also within walking distance to many other attractions including CenturyLink Field, Safeco Field and Pike Place Market.
Wi-Fi is  in all rooms at the The Alexis Royal Sonesta Hotel Seattle. The 100% nonsmoking rooms also feature an honor bar.
The Bookstore Bar & Cafe, located in the The Alexis Royal Sonesta Hotel Seattle, is known for its large whiskey library and monthly scotch tastings. True to its name, guests can also purchase books while they are sipping on a variety of beverages.
Morning coffee and tea service is available in the living room-styled lobby. A fitness center complete with a cardio room and functional fitness room with monkey bars, a bouldering wall, and rings is located at the property. A 24-hour front desk is also provided on site. A concierge service, to assist guests with area attractions, is offered at the hotel.
The Seattle Art Museum is less than 5 minutes’ walk from the The Alexis Royal Sonesta Hotel Seattle. Pike Place Market and the Seattle Waterfront is less than 10 minutes’ walk away. Seattle-Tacoma International Airport is 14 mi away.

name: Hotel Sorrento
description:
Gracing downtown with its breathtaking Italianate architecture for a century, the Sorrento is an oasis of luxury, and one of Seattle’s most recognized and cherished landmarks.
Overlooking the downtown city skyline, the Sorrento is a most unique upscale hotel offering an intimate setting.  As the longest running luxury hotel in Seattle, and recognized as the “grand dame” of Seattle, the Sorrento is defined by legendary hospitality, living up to its reputation as one of the finest hotel destinations in Seattle.
Guests of this hotel will enter through the front entrance, framed with an elegant and lush garden offering couch seating. Fireplaces and table seating with black and cream colored umbrellas are also featured in the lobby's lounge area.
Serving the neighborhood for over 30 years, Dunbar Room bar and restaurant and adjacent Fireside Room are the place to meet on First Hill.

name: Hotel 1000, LXR Hotels & Resorts
description:
Located in downtown Seattle on the corner of First and Madison Street, this 4-star hotel features a full-service spa which offers a number of services such as massages, body treatments, manicures, pedicures, and facials. The Seattle Art Museum is 3 minutes' walk away.
Every room at the 1000 Hotel includes an in-room safe and a mini-bar. The rooms also offer a cable 42-inch flat-screen TV with 52 HD channels, and free Wi-Fi access.
Hotel 1000 provides All Water Seafood & Oyster Bar, an on-site seafood restaurant featuring boat-to-table cuisine sourced from the Pacific Northwest. Bell Lounge is also located on-site, offering craft cocktails and light fare. Virtual golf with over 50 golf courses, a fitness center are available. A business center, meeting facilities, and 24-hour room services can also be found onsite.
The Seattle Center is a 5 minutes' drive away, Pike Place Market is a 7 minutes' walk, and Pioneer Square is a 6 minutes' walk from the hotel.
The Port of Seattle is 2 minutes' drive from Hotel 1000 and it welcomes popular cruise ships. SeaTac International Airport is 14 mi away and the Washington State Convention Center is 17 minutes' walk from the property.

name: W Seattle
description:
Experience all the excitement of Seattle city center at this centrally located hotel, only seconds from major area attractions, and offering unrivaled personalized services along with first-class amenities and luxurious accommodations.
Discover the flying fish and unique shops of Pike Place Market, see stunning views of the skyline from the top of the Space Needle, or admire masterpieces at the Seattle Art Museum, all located close to the W Seattle.  Many corporate offices, including IBM and Morgan Stanley, are also nearby.
Offering on-site dining, Trace Restaurant and Bar features fresh local ingredients and a cocktail menu. The lobby features a three-story fireplace covered in nearly 1,000 stainless steel tiles and topped by a DJ booth as its centerpiece for music Friday and Saturday nights.
The W Seattle offers a large variety of state-of-the-art amenities. Take advantage of the Whatever/Whenever Service, designed to make any dream or wish come true. Enjoy a cocktail at the lobby fireplace, or plan the day with help from the 24-hour concierge service.

description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Hilton Seattle! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Connected via an underground concourse to the Washington State Convention Center, this hotel is moments from top attractions like the Space Needle and features modern amenities, including flat-screen TVs.
Only a few blocks from the Hilton Seattle, guests can discover the famous flying fish of Pike Place Market as well as masterpieces at the Seattle Art Museum. The Seattle Aquarium along with cruise ship terminals and a number of corporate offices are also located nearby.
Guests can also enjoy the on-site fitness center as well as wireless internet access.

name: Arctic Club Hotel
description:
The 10-story Arctic Club Hotel, a historical landmark built in 1916, has been beautifully restored to provide exceptional hospitality, featuring 120 well-appointed rooms for the refined traveler in the heart of downtown Seattle. The Arctic Club Hotel provides unique experiences including the eclectic Polar Bar. The interior and exterior design reflects the era of the Klondike Gold Rush. Live like an icon and experience the adventure of history at the Arctic Club Hotel.
Anchored near Seattle’s historic district on the corner of 3rd Avenue and Cherry Street, the modern Arctic Club Hotel launches explorers into the heart of the city. Walk along the waterfront, venture up the Space Needle, and explore Pike Place Market. Watch the Seahawks or Mariners play down at Lumen Field and T-Mobile Park.
Step into the Polar Bar and take a step back in time to an era where quality and style are one. Lounge in luxurious leather seating surrounded by velvet draperies and choose from a full bar of local wine, craft beer, signature cocktails, or soft drinks. Breakfast will also be served in the Polar Bar.
Stay close to the action with the Columbia Center across the street, Pike Place Market four blocks away and Pioneer Square, T-Mobile Park, and Lumen Field within a 10-minute walk. With the Link light rail stop right in front of the hotel continuing the adventure downtown and beyond is as simple as hopping on.

userReviews.positive: The hotel is very charming and was in a good location for walking around Seattle. The desk staff that night and the next morning were very nice.
userReviews.negative:
The room was a little dark. Some of that was just the style but it could have used a few more lights. Our room faced out over the HVAC units and there was a constant hum. It wasn't bad but some people might prefer a different location. Wifi was a little spotty at first - they had to reboot the router. We got off of the light rail less than a block away from the hotel. It was after dark and there were a number of people huddled across the street which was a little concerning. We wanted to go out to eat but didnt want to attempt to locate a restaurant so we ate in the bar at the hotel. The prices were pretty high and the service was nothing exceptional.
Also, there was an additional Seattle city tax added to the price, so the price you see on the search is actually much higher. I would rather they just add that in to the price you see during the search.

userReviews.positive:
The historic decor was wonderful.  The main floor gathering area was a destination in itself. Great for relaxing around the fireplace and meeting with friends.  Every staff member we came in contact was very friendly and went out of their way to acknowledge us and ask if we needed anything.
The public transportation nearby was great.  There is a light rail station 1/2 block away that will get you to the SeaTac airport and many other destinations around Seattle.  Many downtown bus options on the same block. No need for a car.  Also close access to the Ferry terminal with car ferries and Fast Ferry passenger ferries to many destinations around the sound.

userReviews.positive: I loved the feel of this classic hotel.. The breakfast didn't have a lot of items but it was satisfying. They had pastries & fruit, juice and coffee available. The staff overall were very attentive which I gather was because they had just reopened after a long closure and they didn't have high occupancy at the time. The room was very nice, jacuzzi tub - amazing. Spacious room with bed & desk. I was very comfortable.
userReviews.negative: My hairdryer didn't work at all. I had some trouble with the printer in the business center because the duplex feed didn't work and it kept jamming. I could tell the printers hadn't been upgraded for quite a long time. The hotel overall needs some maintenance work, but nothing except what I noted here was actually broken. The toilet in my room was a bit sluggish but water worked and everything was clean. I reported to the hotel that I had a hard time finding information about parking options at the hotel. It turned out they did have valet, but I couldn't find anything mentioning that online so I parked in a garage about 3 blocks away for almost the same price as valet :(. I wasn't super happy but wasn't about to move my car.

name: Fairmont Olympic Hotel
description:
Listed on the National Register of Historic Places, this downtown Seattle hotel features multiple onsite award-winning dining options. Rooms offer city views with French-inspired furnishings.
Cable TV and a mini-bar are featured in each guest room at the Fairmont Olympic Hotel. The private bathroom offers designer toiletries and terry robes. The windows in each room open to allow fresh air in.
A fitness center and indoor pool is available for guests. A 24-hour concierge service is offered to provide guests with assistance on area attractions. Many on site shops are available at the Fairmont Olympic.
The 5th Avenue Theater is across the street from the hotel. The Washington State Convention Center is 5 minutes’ walk away. Pike Place Market is just 10 minutes’ walk from the property.

name: Executive Hotel Pacific
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Executive Hotel Pacific! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
This European style hotel in downtown Seattle is 15 minutes’ monorail ride from the Space Needle. It features free WiFi, an on-site restaurant, fitness center, and contemporary rooms with plush bathrobes and complimentary bath products.
Every room at the Executive Hotel Pacific is furnished with a 42 inch flat-screen cable TV. Also included is a 15-inch laptop safe and an in-room coffee machine.
The Lodge Sports Grille restaurant within the hotel provides guests with warm, lodge ambiance and serves burgers, steaks, sandwiches, salads, and a happy hour with local craft beer. Guests can enjoy a daily wine reception on the mezzanine level.
Executive Hotel Pacific Seattle is 2 blocks from University Street Tunnel Station. It is within 15 minutes’ walk from the Seattle Art Museum, Seattle Aquarium and Pike Place Market. SeaTac International Airport is within 25 minutes' drive and the Washington State Convention Center is within 10 minutes' walk.

userReviews.negative:
The downtown location was too quiet in terms of restaurants and cafes--most, including even Starbucks, were closed on weekends (or at least on the Saturday we were there), we assume because it's a Monday-Friday business district. Getting to places we wanted to go required longer and hilly walks that were sometimes difficult.
Although the room was quiet, lovely and beautify, the mirrored walls were excessive, especially on the toilet room door.  It is not pleasant to see yourself toileting, nor to have to see yourself virtually everywhere in the room.
Finally, the rate is very pricey. It's hard to quite say that it's a "value" from the rate perspective even though it was exceptional in most regards.

name: Kimpton Hotel Vintage Seattle, an IHG Hotel
description:
15 minutes’ walk to Pike Place Market, Kimpton Hotel Vintage Seattle in the heart of Seattle features a nightly hosted wine hour.
Furnished in rich tones reflecting the nearby Washington Wine Country, rooms offer a flat-screen TV, in-room safe, and mini-bar. Premium bath amenities, a hair dryer, an iron and ironing board, and bathrobe are included.
In addition to the 24-hour fitness center, guests can take advantage of the "Om Away From Home" in-room yoga program with the Yoga Channel on every TV.
Pioneer Square, the Waterfront Neighborhood, the Washington State Convention and Trade Center, and the Seattle Public Library are all within 1 mi from Kimpton Hotel Vintage Seattle.

name: La Quinta by Wyndham Seattle Downtown
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at La Quinta by Wyndham Seattle Downtown! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located 1 miles away from the Seattle Space Needle, this hotel features a fitness center and serves a daily continental breakfast. Limited parking is available to guests on a first-come, first-serve basis. All rooms are equipped with free Wi-Fi.
A flat-screen cable TV is provided in each air-conditioned guest room at La Quinta Inn & Suites Seattle Downtown. For convenience, all rooms feature a coffee maker, ironing facilities and a hairdryer.
A 24-hour reception greets guests of Seattle Downtown La Quinta.  A guest launderette and a business center are available. A convenience store is located in the hotel.
T-Mobile Park, home of the Seattle Mariners professional baseball team, is 3 miles away from this hotel. The University of Washington is 10 minutes’ drive away.

name: Level Seattle Downtown - South Lake Union
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Level Seattle Downtown - South Lake Union! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Ideally set in the center of Seattle, Level Seattle Downtown - South Lake Union provides 4-star accommodations close to Space Needle and Westlake Center. Ideally located in the South Lake Union district, this hotel has a terrace, as well as a sauna and a hot tub. The property has a seasonal outdoor pool, indoor pool, fitness center and shared lounge.

userReviews.title: Overall, Level Seattle exceeded our expectations, but don't count on the TVs.
userReviews.positive: I had no idea how much it was like getting our own little apartment for our week stay, but it really was! We had a washer and dryer, dishwasher, stove/oven, the works. The balcony and view were great, and the kids liked the family room (which included an indoor playroom more for little ones like my 1-year-old and an outdoor playground more for my 4-year-old, 6-year-old, and 8-year-old including climbing rock walls). There was lots of gym space for working out and a pool as well, though we didn't get a chance to use those. We were able to check in early without issue, which was very appreciated.
userReviews.negative: We were pleasantly surprised by the large flatscreen TV in the livingroom and in the main bedroom, at first... except they didn't work very well. We rarely got the bedroom TV to function at all, and the one in the livingroom was always freezing up, randomly losing volume, or changing channels. I think it might have to do with all the rooms probably having the same brand/type of TVs and remotes, and possibly other travelers operating their TVs disrupts TVs in other rooms? I'm not sure what the problem is, but my 4-year-old was frequently frustrated by it. Also, the balcony door has to be slammed--HARD--to shut. I'm not sure if it is a matter of the metal door swelling or being slightly too high in its frame, but the top of the frame catches it and makes it difficult to close it.

userReviews.title: Choose Level for your next visit to Seattle.
userReviews.positive: The staff were available and happy to answer questions right away before and during our stay. Our room was upgraded from Deluxe to Executive at no charge, so that's always great. Enough amenities to not have to leave the hotel. Exceptional place to choose for anybody visiting Seattle.

name: The Mediterranean Inn
description:
Located just 10 minutes' walk away from The Space Needle, The Mediterranean Inn features a rooftop patio with panoramic views of the Seattle Skyline, Mount Rainier, the Olympic Mountains, and Elliot Bay. A fitness center is located on site.
All guest rooms at this hotel include a flat-screen TV, full sized work desk, a microwave, small refrigerator, coffee maker, and kitchenette. All rooms include private bathrooms that include hairdryers.
A 24-hour reception greets guests of The Mediterranean Inn.  A business center and 24-hour laundry facilities are provided to guests. Vending machines featuring snacks and drinks are available. Coffee is available in the lobby.
Pike Place Market is 1.2 mi away from this hotel. Hosting sports and entertainment events, KeyArena is 3 minutes’ walk away.

name: Homewood Suites by Hilton Seattle Downtown
description:
Offering views of Puget Sound and located within walking distance from major city center attractions, this all-suite hotel features spacious accommodations, furnished with fully equipped kitchens.
View the city from the top of the Space Needle, stroll along the waterfront or visit the Seattle Center Arts and Entertainment Complex, only steps from the Homewood Suites Seattle Downtown. A number of cruise ship terminals as well as the corporate offices of F5 Networks, Holland America and Emeritus are also nearby.
After a restful night's sleep in the spacious 2 room suites, start the morning at the Downtown Seattle Homewood Suites with a free hot breakfast buffet. A state-of-the-art fitness center is provided. Please join the evening reception held on select nights, offering complimentary drinks and great conversation.

name: Staypineapple, The Maxwell Hotel, Seattle Center Seattle
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Staypineapple, The Maxwell Hotel, Seattle Center Seattle! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located within walking distance of Seattle’s Space Needle, Staypineapple, The Maxwell Hotel, Seattle Center Seattle offers original artwork and colorful interiors. Guests can enjoy free access to the indoor pool and the fitness room. Each guest room features wood floors, free WiFi and a 42-inch flat-screen TV.
Guest rooms at this hotel are decorated in bold colors and are equipped with an iHome Bluetooth docking station. A refrigerator, microwave and gourmet coffee maker are provided in every room. Private bathrooms boast marble counter tops, designer toiletries, bathrobes, and a walk-in shower.
Staypineapple, The Maxwell Hotel, Seattle Center Seattle features an espresso stand offering smoothies, coffee, and snacks to-go. Guests can enjoy complimentary coffee and pineapple treats in the afternoon. A business center is also located onsite, while bicycles are available for guest use.
Just 8 minutes' walk from this hotel is the Seattle Center Monorail, offering easy access to downtown.  The Seattle Aquarium is 1.9 miles from the hotel, and the Washington State Convention Center is 1.8 miles away.

name: Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle Downtown/Lake Union
description:
This Seattle hotel, located on Lake Union, offers modern rooms with free Wi-Fi and a daily hot breakfast. The Ferd Hutchinson Cancer Research Center is directly across from the hotel.
All guest rooms at Residence Inn Seattle Downtown/Lake Union offer a 32-inch flat-screen TV.  Each room has a fully equipped kitchen fitted with cooking utensils, fridge and stove. All rooms have a private balcony. Some rooms boast panoramic views of Lake Union.
Guests are welcome to take a swim in the indoor pool or relax in the hotel's hot tub.  The fitness center offers treadmills and free weights for active guests. Children will stay entertained thanks to the on-site children's activity center. Laundry and dry cleaning services are also available.
Residence Inn Seattle Downtown is a 10 minutes' streetcar ride from Westlake Shopping Center. Washington State Convention and Trade Center is 1.3 miles away.

userReviews.title: Wish we stayed longer!
userReviews.positive: Apart from the traffic to get here from the ferry port, this hotel is in a great location. It was just a quick drive from where we wanted to visit (Dinos’ Alive), and right across the street is a  Yacht place with beautiful water views! The bed was really comfy to us, and having the suite was great for our toddler to have space to roam. The kitchen was great for saving money on not needing to dine out (except no oven) but I was able to cook on the stovetop & microwave, and store all our cold foods in the full size fridge. The free breakfast is also really great, a lot of choices! The playroom was fun for us. Didn’t swim or workout, but the gym is way nicer than other places we’ve stayed and 24/7. The staff were all super nice and accommodating and even got us a room up higher for a better view! Depending on where your room is from the elevator, you will be walking a lot but the elevators are pretty fast. The lobby is real pretty with a nice fountain and many places to sit. Didn’t visit the little bar/pizza place, but it looked nice too. The balcony is quite small, but we still enjoyed sitting out there and taking in the nighttime city lights. It was also quieter than expected, which was nice. I would definitely stay here again!

name: Hyatt House Seattle Downtown
description:
Set across the street from Seattle’s famous Space Needle, Hyatt House Seattle Downtown features bright and contemporary guest accommodations complete with individual kitchen amenities. Complimentary WiFi access are available at this hotel.
Each air-conditioned guest room here provides a terrace, a seating area with a sofa and a flat-screen TV, and an iPod docking station. Kitchenware, a refrigerator, a microwave, and a coffee machine are included.
Guests at Hyatt House Seattle Downtown can take advantage of the fitness center, or relax after a long day with a drink and light fare at the on-site bar. A business center and a mini-market are also available at the hotel. Guests can take advantage of a free shuttle within 1 mi of the property. A complimentary hot breakfast including made-to-order omelets is served daily.
The hotel is a 3-minute walk from the Museum of Pop Culture and a 10-minute walk from the Olympic Sculpture Park. The city center of Seattle is 0.6 mi from the property, and Seattle-Tacoma International Airport is located 15 mi away.

Staybridge Suites Seattle - South Lake Union is located in the South Lake Union district of Seattle, and is 0.7 mi from Space Needle. Only steps from downtown Seattle's most popular attractions, including the Space Needle, this luxurious hotel features state-of-the-art amenities, exceptional accommodations and unrivaled facilities, all in the heart of the city.

name: Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Seattle Downtown/Seattle Center
description:
Well located in Seattle, Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Seattle Downtown/Seattle Center provides air-conditioned rooms, a fitness center and free WiFi. The property is located 4.7 km from CenturyLink Field, 29 km from Tiger Mountain State Forest and a 14-minute walk from Westlake Center. Private parking is available on site.
Each room has a TV, and certain rooms at the hotel have a city view. Guest rooms will provide guests with a fridge.
Breakfast is available daily, and includes buffet, continental and American options.
A business center is at guests' disposal at Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Seattle Downtown/Seattle Center. With staff speaking English and Spanish, guidance is available at the reception.
Popular points of interest near the accommodation include Pocket Beach, Space Needle and Museum of Pop Culture. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 1 km from Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Seattle Downtown/Seattle Center.

We had a lot of luggage so we couldn’t just take a regular taxi or Uber. It was complete chaos trying to scramble to leave the hotel as a result and we almost missed the ferry. Worth staying there just don’t rely on the front desk for info!

name: Seattle Marriott Waterfront
description:
This waterfront hotel, located in downtown Seattle along Elliott Bay, is a 5-minute walk to the Seattle Aquarium. The upscale hotel features newly renovated nautical rooms, indoor/outdoor connecting pool and rooms with a refrigerator.
The elegant rooms at Seattle Marriott Waterfront are equipped with a 42-inch flat-screen TV, coffee maker and a work desk. Every bathroom is spacious and many rooms have private balconies with bay and mountain views.
Seattle Marriott Waterfront offers a 24-hour modern gym and a full-service business center. Concierge services are available to help arrange tours, reservations and other activities.
Waterfront Marriott Seattle’s restaurant, Hook & Plow is open all day and serves American and regional dishes.
The Bell Harbor International Conference Center is located across the street. Pike Place Market is a 7-minute walk from the Waterfront hotel. The Space Needle is less than a 5-minute drive away, and SeaTac International Airport is within 25 minutes' drive.

name: Holiday Inn Seattle DWTN Lake Union, an IHG Hotel
description:
Only a few blocks from the famous Space Needle and Pike's Place Market, this central Seattle hotel offers amenities such as a full-service restaurant and on-site fitness center.
Holiday Inn Seattle Downtown features free wireless internet access throughout the entire hotel. Guests will also appreciate the hotel's newsstand as well as the well-equipped business center. After a busy day, guests can relax with a home-style meal in the Emerald Grill and Lounge.
The guestrooms at the Holiday Inn Seattle Downtown offer conveniences such as a work desk with an ergonomic chair. Guests can enjoy a restful night's sleep with the comfortable bed and pillow menu.

name: Staypineapple, Hotel FIVE, Downtown Seattle
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Staypineapple, Hotel FIVE, Downtown Seattle! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Free bicycles are available for guest use at this downtown Seattle eco-friendly hotel. Modern rooms at Hotel FIVE feature an iHome Bluetooth docking station and free Wi-Fi. The Seattle Center and the Seattle Space Needle are 10 minutes’ walk away.
A flat-screen cable TV is available in all brightly furnished guest rooms at Hotel FIVE. A work desk and gourmet coffee machine are included, along with complimentary bottled water. Designer toiletries and a bathrobe are also featured.
Afternoon refreshments are served daily in the hotel lobby. Guests can enjoy a pineapple treat and free coffee every afternoon at Seattle Hotel FIVE.
A 24-hour fitness center is available for guest convenience. Dry cleaning services are offered.
Pike Place Market and the Seattle Waterfront are less than 1 miles away from this hotel. Safeco Field is less than 10 minutes’ drive away.

A seating area with a sofa and a flat-screen cable TV is featured in all guest rooms at the SpringHill Suites Seattle Downtown. A work desk and an iPod docking station are also included.
The Bistro on Yale Bar offers evening cocktails and a large beer and wine selection. Happy hour is available from 4:00 pm until 7:00 pm. The Bistro on Yale Restaurant at Seattle downtown SpringHill Suites offers fresh, regional cuisine.
A fitness center is available.
The Washington State Convention Center is less than 5 minutes’ drive from the hotel. Pike Place Market is less than 10 minutes’ drive away.

name: The Edgewater, a Noble House Hotel
description:
Located on Seattle's waterfront at Pier 67, The Edgewater hotel features guest rooms with views of Elliott Bay and the Olympic Mountains. A complimentary shuttle service within downtown Seattle is offered at the property.
The hotel features guest rooms and suites fitted with gas fireplaces, knotty pine furniture, and leather chairs. Each room includes an European-style spa bathroom with complimentary bath amenities. Additional features include an in-room coffee machine, mini-bar, and views of downtown Seattle or the Puget Sound.
Guests can work out at the on-site fitness center, outfitted with cardio machines, free weights, and additional exercise equipment. Selling various Seattle souvenirs and collectibles, the on-site gift shop, known as 'Shop...on The Edge,' features an on-site coffee bar.
Six Seven, a full-service restaurant, is located on-site and offers seasonal Pacific Northwest cuisine and views of the Puget Sound and surrounding mountains.
Pike Place Market is within 15 minutes' walk of The Edgewater Hotel, while the Space Needle is within 20 minutes' walk. The Seattle Aquarium is 1 mi away, while the Seattle Ferry Terminal for the Victoria Clipper is within 5 minutes' walk. The nearest airport is SeaTac International Airport, approximately 14 mi away.

name: The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection
description:
Located in Seattle, one mile from Pocket Beach, The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection provides accommodations with a fitness center, private parking, a terrace and a bar. This 4-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk, a business center and free WiFi. The property is 1,800 feet from the city center and a 10-minute walk from Space Needle.
The hotel will provide guests with air-conditioned rooms with a closet, a coffee machine, a fridge, a safety deposit box, a flat-screen TV and a private bathroom with a shower. At The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection all rooms are equipped with bed linen and towels.
Breakfast is available every morning, and includes à la carte, continental and American options. At the accommodation you'll find a restaurant serving American cuisine. Vegetarian, vegan and dairy-free options can also be requested.
Popular points of interest near The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection include Westlake Center, Museum of Pop Culture and Washington State Convention Center. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 1.2 miles from the hotel.

description:
Located in downtown Seattle, this hotel is 3 blocks from the Space Needle and features a 24-hour breakfast bar with made-to-order and prepackaged items. Its rooms have alarm clocks with MP3 docking stations.
Hyatt Place Seattle Downtown has spacious, air-conditioned rooms with a 42-inch, flat-screen TV and a refrigerator. Wi-Fi is free in all rooms and the living area includes a sofa bed.
Guests can work out in the gym or swim in the indoor pool. The 100% smoke-free hotel has a business center.
Hyatt Place is less than a mile from the Seattle Center, housing local attractions including Key Arena, Fun Forest Amusement Park and the Science Fiction Museum. SeaTac International Airport is 15 miles away.

name: The ART INN Seattle
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at The ART INN Seattle! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
The ART INN Seattle is located in Seattle, 1.5 miles from CenturyLink Field and 2.1 miles from Space Needle. Featuring a garden, the inn is close to several noted attractions, around a 18-minute walk from Seattle Center Monorail, 0.8 miles from Columbia Center and 1.1 miles from King Street Station. The accommodation offers a business center for guest use.
Tiger Mountain State Forest is 16 miles from The ART INN Seattle, while Washington State Convention Center is 1.1 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 2.5 miles from the inn.

description:

At the hotel, the rooms have a desk, a flat-screen TV, a private bathroom, bed linen and towels. Each room comes with a safety deposit box and some have city views. All rooms will provide guests with a fridge.
Guests at Astra Hotel, Seattle, A Tribute Portfolio Hotel by Marriott can enjoy an American breakfast.
The area is popular for hiking and cycling, and car rental is available at this 4-star hotel.
There's an in-house bar and guests can also use the business area.
Popular points of interest near the accommodation include Space Needle, Museum of Pop Culture and Westlake Center. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 0.6 miles from Astra Hotel, Seattle, A Tribute Portfolio Hotel by Marriott.

userReviews.title: Could be great, new facility problems to sort through.
userReviews.positive: Great location, modern building, good design.
userReviews.negative:
Problems with amenities. At no point could we figure out how to get the elevator to take us to the bar, which was a huge reason we booked this spot for our anniversary. A light broke and was throwing sparks within 20 minutes of checking in. The staff was quick to move us into a new room for our safety, but the ice machine didn’t work on that floor which made keeping my boyfriend’s insulin cold a challenge. They thought the fridges had freezers for his ice packs but they don’t, which may be a dealbreaker in the future. We really liked everything else but it’s really important when we’re traveling that my boyfriend is able to keep frozen icepacks for his insulin when we’re out and about.
All the issues seemed like kinks still being ironed out since we could tell the hotel was brand new. As Kraken fans from Portland, we’d love to give it another shot and make this our regular game day stay.

userReviews.title: Pretentious but clean and friendly
userReviews.positive:
obviously I liked the view of the Space Needle. we had a King corner room and the views were spectacular. Extremely clean. I loved the daily housekeeping, a rarity these days. Streetcar station right outside the hotel. Staff were friendly and accommodating,
especially Peyton in Ladro Cafe.
Breakfast food was delicious but limited choices.
userReviews.negative:
Let’s start with the breakfast. Delivious, but only 5 options - no American breakfast nor continental breakfast, no fresh fruit- that gets old after a few days. I would not include breakfast in my room choice anymore.
It’s pretentious. Everything is laid out prettily for perfect IG pics and not for guest comfort. The room was supposed to be 335squft, trust me it was not. when someone works at the desk you have to climb over the bed to get past them.
Toiletries still supplied in small plastic tubes, really? and they get mixed and matched randomly so that you end up with two body lotions but no shampoo or body wash. No biggie but annoying.
Heating is very loud.
Small room despite upgrades. Loved the colorful electric blinds but 
Lots of little tech gadgets like a plug in night light and shades don’t make up for a  basically cheaply equipped room.
Zero parking to unload your luggage. If street parking is full you have to circle. 
Staff is not knowledgeable about the area. Michelle gave us completely wrong information and even marked the wrong public transport staton on a map we asked for. We later figured it out ourselves that there is an app to navigate easily. 
She also gave us room keys that were not working. And forgot to give us breakfast vouchers. All small but annoying things that cost you time in your day.
rooftop bar: I’m sure it’s super chill in summer but you can’t access it as a hotel guest to just enjoy the view. You  need to first go down to the lobby, check in with a reservation at the desk and then they let you go up. Pretentious at best. The vibe was meh, charcuterie board looked like a teenager arranged it and bar was not fully stocked. Limited cocktail choices. Tried to go up there in the afternoon to take pictures and you can’t. 
Not worth the money unless you want to take endless IG selfies and are looking for a nice backdrop. It does  not feel luxurious at all.
userReviews.room: Space Needle View, Corner with 1 King Bed

name: Warwick Seattle
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Warwick Seattle! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located just a 7 minutes' walk from the famous Pike Place Market, this 18-story hotel features an on-site restaurant. An indoor pool and whirlpool is also provided. A full continental breakfast is served daily.
Boasting unique accommodations inspired by Seattle culture, the spacious rooms of the Warwick Seattle feature private Juliet balconies and floor-to-ceiling windows. A refrigerator/mini-bar and coffee/tea makers are included.
Margaux at the Warwick provides an eclectic menu, simply described as Northwestern cuisine, combining ingredients and elements of Northwest-style cooking with local influences and accent in a casual atmosphere. Guests can enjoy breakfast, lunch, and dinner at the restaurant, also open for weekend brunch. The Margaux Lounge features a full-service bar and a lighter menu.
A 24-hour fitness centre is open to all guests, and features treadmills, an elliptical, a recumbent bicycle, free weights, and more. The business centre and weekday laundry services are also available.
The Warwick Seattle is 4 blocks from downtown Seattle. The Space Needle and Seattle Center are just 8 blocks away.

name: citizenM Seattle South Lake Union
description:
Located conveniently in the South Lake Union district of Seattle, citizenM Seattle South Lake Union is set 0.6 mi from Space Needle, 0.9 mi from Seattle Center and 0.9 mi from Pike Place Market. Among the facilities of this property are a restaurant, a 24-hour front desk and a shared lounge, along with free WiFi throughout the property. The property is close to popular attractions like Port of Seattle, KeyArena and International Fountain.
The hotel will provide guests with air-conditioned rooms offering a desk, a safety deposit box, a flat-screen TV and a private bathroom with a shower.
With the room iPad, or the free citizenM app, all guests can control room lights, black-out blinds, curtains, temperature, as well as TV and radio channels. They can also stream from their own Netflix, Prime or Disney+ accounts (and many others), by connecting their phone, tablet or laptop to the TV via Chromecast (at no extra charge).
At citizenM Seattle South Lake Union all rooms are equipped with bed linen and towels.
The accommodations offers a buffet or vegetarian breakfast.
A business center and ironing facilities are available at citizenM Seattle South Lake Union.
Popular points of interest near the hotel include Museum of Pop Culture, Washington State Convention Center and Westlake Center. The nearest airport is Boeing Field/King County International Airport, 7.5 mi from citizenM Seattle South Lake Union.

name: Hotel Andra Seattle MGallery Hotel Collection
description:
This luxury boutique hotel is in the heart of downtown Seattle located between the popular Belltown district and Lake Union. The hotel is within a 6 minutes' walk from famous Pike Place Market and Westlake Shopping Center. Hotel Ändra offers complimentary Wi-Fi.
All rooms at Hotel Ändra feature subtle Scandinavian decor and include a 37" flat-screen TV, clock radio with Bluetooth pairing capabilities, ironing facilities, a private bar with premium spirits and a coffee maker. The bathrooms include plush spa bathrobes, luxury bath amenities and a hairdryer.
Hotel Ändra features Lola Restaurant, which serves Greek and Pacific Northwest cuisine. Assaggio Ristorante features authentic Northern Italian cuisine. Both restaurants offer room service.
Guests can work out in the on-site fitness center or take advantage of the hotel's discounts to nearby fitness clubs.
Hotel Ändra is a 15-minute walk from The Seattle Center and Space Needle. SeaTac International Airport is 15 mi from the hotel.

name: Silver Cloud Hotel - Seattle Stadium
description:
This Seattle hotel is located across the street from T-Mobile Park, home of the Seattle Mariners, and next to Lumen Field, home of the Seattle Seahawks and Seattle Sounders. Free Wi-Fi is available in every guest room.
The modern, warm colored rooms feature a 55-inch flat-screen TV with cable channels and an iPod clock radio. A microwave, fridge and coffee maker are also included. Complimentary designer toiletries are offered in the private bathroom.
Guests at Silver Cloud Hotel - Seattle Stadium can swim in the rooftop pool that overlooks Elliot Bay and T-Mobile Park. They can also relax in the hot tub or work out in the fitness center.
Seattle Stadium Silver Cloud Hotel features Jimmy’s on First, an upscale restaurant with a casual atmosphere. Pacific Northwest cuisine, cocktails, and premium beers are featured.
Two light rail stations are 1 block away. The hotel is 3 blocks from Seattle’s waterfront.

name: La Quinta by Wyndham Seattle Downtown
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at La Quinta by Wyndham Seattle Downtown! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located 1 miles away from the Seattle Space Needle, this hotel features a fitness center and serves a daily continental breakfast. Limited parking is available to guests on a first-come, first-serve basis. All rooms are equipped with free Wi-Fi.
A flat-screen cable TV is provided in each air-conditioned guest room at La Quinta Inn & Suites Seattle Downtown. For convenience, all rooms feature a coffee maker, ironing facilities and a hairdryer.
A 24-hour reception greets guests of Seattle Downtown La Quinta.  A guest launderette and a business center are available. A convenience store is located in the hotel.
T-Mobile Park, home of the Seattle Mariners professional baseball team, is 3 miles away from this hotel. The University of Washington is 10 minutes’ drive away.

name: Kimpton Palladian Hotel, an IHG Hotel
description:
Offering a restaurant on-site, Kimpton Palladian Hotel is located in Seattle. Guest rooms feature pop-art pillows while certain units have a claw footed bathtub. The hotel is 1,000 feet from Pike Place Market and 0.6 mi from the Space Needle.
Each air-conditioned room here will provide you with a satellite TV with pay-per-view channels.TV, an iPod docking station and a mini-bar. Featuring a bathrobe and free Bigelow bath amenities, the private bathrooms come with a hairdryer.
An evening wine hour is held every night from 17:00 to 18:00 at Kimpton Palladian Hotel. Free bikes are also available. Other facilities offered at the property include meeting facilities, luggage storage and dry cleaning.
Guests can enjoy bold flavors at the hotel’s seafood restaurant, Shaker + Spear.
Sea-Tac Airport is 12 mi away. The Washington State Convention Center as well as the Seattle’s waterfront can be reached within 12 minutes' walk. Safeco Field is 1.9 mi from the Kimpton Palladian Hotel.

description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Hotel Max! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
This design hotel in downtown Seattle is 1 block from the Westlake Ave & Olive Way Light Rail station. Hotel Max features original paintings and photographs by Seattle artists.
The contemporary rooms, decorated with paintings, offer a flat-screen cable TV, Bluetooth clock radio, and local mini-bar. The bathrooms offer bathrobes and complimentary toiletries. Guests can take advantage of the in-room fitness amenities, including streamed online workout videos, a yoga mat, resistance bands, weights, and a core ball.
During their stay, guests can workout in the 24-hour fitness center. Bicycle rentals are available for guests to explore the city.
Hotel Max is within 1 miles of the Seattle Aquarium, Space Needle and Olympic Sculpture Park.

userReviews.title: Overall, Level Seattle exceeded our expectations, but don't count on the TVs.
userReviews.positive: I had no idea how much it was like getting our own little apartment for our week stay, but it really was! We had a washer and dryer, dishwasher, stove/oven, the works. The balcony and view were great, and the kids liked the family room (which included an indoor playroom more for little ones like my 1-year-old and an outdoor playground more for my 4-year-old, 6-year-old, and 8-year-old including climbing rock walls). There was lots of gym space for working out and a pool as well, though we didn't get a chance to use those. We were able to check in early without issue, which was very appreciated.
userReviews.negative: We were pleasantly surprised by the large flatscreen TV in the livingroom and in the main bedroom, at first... except they didn't work very well. We rarely got the bedroom TV to function at all, and the one in the livingroom was always freezing up, randomly losing volume, or changing channels. I think it might have to do with all the rooms probably having the same brand/type of TVs and remotes, and possibly other travelers operating their TVs disrupts TVs in other rooms? I'm not sure what the problem is, but my 4-year-old was frequently frustrated by it. Also, the balcony door has to be slammed--HARD--to shut. I'm not sure if it is a matter of the metal door swelling or being slightly too high in its frame, but the top of the frame catches it and makes it difficult to close it.

userReviews.title: Choose Level for your next visit to Seattle.
userReviews.positive: The staff were available and happy to answer questions right away before and during our stay. Our room was upgraded from Deluxe to Executive at no charge, so that's always great. Enough amenities to not have to leave the hotel. Exceptional place to choose for anybody visiting Seattle.

description:

Pacific Science Center is 10 minutes’ walk from Belltown Inn. Seattle Art Museum is 15 minutes’ walk away.

name: Thompson Seattle
description:
Offering a terrace and views of the sea, Thompson Seattle is set in Seattle. Guests can enjoy the on-site rooftop bar, and complimentary high-speed Wi-Fi.
The rooms include a 42" flat-screen TV with a customized movie library. Some rooms feature a seating area for your convenience. The beds are complimented with 400 thread count SFERRA linens. The private bathrooms include state-of-the-art rain showers and soaking tubs, D.S. & DURGA luxury bath amenities, and over-sized Frette bathrobes.
Boasting views of Elliott Bay and the Olympic Mountains, The Nest is the rooftop bar and cocktail lounge located on-site at Thompson Seattle. You will find a 24-hour front desk and shops at the property.
Pike Place Market is 350 feet from Thompson Seattle, while Pike Place Market is 650 feet from the property. Sea-Tac Airport is 12 mi away.

name: Pan Pacific Seattle
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Pan Pacific Seattle! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Only steps from downtown Seattle's most popular attractions, including the Space Needle, this luxurious hotel features state-of-the-art amenities, exceptional accommodations and unrivaled facilities, all in the heart of the city.
Discover the shopping of Pike Street, visit the Washington State Convention Center or enjoy stunning views from the Space Needle, all within walking distance of the Pan Pacific Seattle. World-renowned restaurants, numerous entertainment options and a vibrant nightlife can also be found only steps from the hotel's front doors.
Enjoy gourmet dining at the on-site restaurant. After a long day, relax in spacious guestrooms, furnished with luxurious linens and plasma-screen TVs. A complimentary shuttle within a 2 miles radius is offered at the Pan Pacific Seattle hotel. Seattle-Tacoma International Airport is 15 miles away.

name: Inn at the Market
description:
Overlooking Elliott Bay and in the heart of Seattle's vibrant Pike Place Market, this boutique hotel has an on-site bar and sweeping views from the rooftop deck. The rooms include free Wi-Fi.
Cable TV is provided in each room at the Inn at the Market. A small fridge, a minibar, and views of the city are also featured.
Various shops are available at the hotel and a 24-hour front desk is provided for guest convenience. Dry cleaning and laundry services are provided at the Seattle Inn at the Market and a business center is available for guest use.
The Olympic Sculpture Park is less than a 20-minute walk from the hotel. The Space Needle is 1.6 km from the hotel. Safeco Field and CenturyLink Field are both 2.4 km from the property.

name: Seattle Marriott Waterfront
description:
This waterfront hotel, located in downtown Seattle along Elliott Bay, is a 5-minute walk to the Seattle Aquarium. The upscale hotel features newly renovated nautical rooms, indoor/outdoor connecting pool and rooms with a refrigerator.
The elegant rooms at Seattle Marriott Waterfront are equipped with a 42-inch flat-screen TV, coffee maker and a work desk. Every bathroom is spacious and many rooms have private balconies with bay and mountain views.
Seattle Marriott Waterfront offers a 24-hour modern gym and a full-service business center. Concierge services are available to help arrange tours, reservations and other activities.
Waterfront Marriott Seattle’s restaurant, Hook & Plow is open all day and serves American and regional dishes.
The Bell Harbor International Conference Center is located across the street. Pike Place Market is a 7-minute walk from the Waterfront hotel. The Space Needle is less than a 5-minute drive away, and SeaTac International Airport is within 25 minutes' drive.

name: Mayflower Park Hotel
description:
Built in 1927, this historic hotel located in the center of Seattle is within a 10 minute walk to Pike Place Market. It features Andaluca Restaurant and Oliver’s Lounge. All guest rooms are decorated with traditional furnishings, and free Wi-Fi is available throughout the entire property.
Guest rooms at the Mayflower Park Hotel provide a flat-screen cable TV and a desk. The bathrooms include original tiled floors, luxurious bathrobes and soaker tubs.
The fitness center includes cardio equipment and weights. Foreign currency exchange services are available.
Andaluca Restaurant serves Northwest cuisine with a Mediterranean theme. Oliver’s Lounge offers signature martinis and light meals.
The Washington State Convention and Trade Center is 4 blocks from Mayflower Hotel. The hotel offers direct access to the monorail with service to the Space Needle and the Seattle Center.

name: Mint House Seattle - Downtown
description:
A 18-minute walk from Space Needle, Mint House Seattle - Downtown is located in Seattle and provides free WiFi and concierge services. The property is around 17 miles from Tiger Mountain State Forest, a 12-minute walk from Seattle Center Monorail and half a mile from Washington State Convention Center. The property is one mile from Pocket Beach, and within 1,200 feet of the city center.
All guest rooms are equipped with an oven, microwave, an electric tea pot, a bath, a hairdryer and a closet. Every room comes with a coffee machine and a private bathroom with a shower and free toiletries, while some rooms here will provide you with a kitchen equipped with a fridge. At the hotel rooms include bed linen and towels.
Popular points of interest near Mint House Seattle - Downtown include CenturyLink Field, Seattle Great Wheel and Seattle Aquarium. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 1.2 miles from the accommodation.

userReviews.title: INVESTED WITH GIANT ROACHES
userReviews.positive: I like the location.
userReviews.negative: My wife had found an adult size roach in the bath room while she was on the toilet. She screamed and I thought she was joking, until I saw her off the toilet and standing in the shower. She was right, and I couldn't believe this was actually happening on our anniversary. We missed out on a 200 dollar reservation at the space needle that we can not get back. I immediately closed the bath room door, cover the bottom of the door with a towel until I found a resolution. My wife did not want to stay in that room anymore let alone the hotel. I called customer service to get support and yes they were helpful but took longer than I expected. They upgraded our room, and got us out of there within an hour and an half. We survived the night, but my wife was beyond paranoid, and It made the rest of the night difficult. However, when we first arrive the room was nice, and it was pretty hot as well. There's no AC. I had asked for accommodations for our anniversary. They provided us with petals on the bed, flowers in a vase and red wine with chocolate. All which were about $45, which is exactly the refund option they offered to give us for the inconvenience. I'm not a fan of bugs let alone roaches, so when I see one I assume there's more. I would not stay here, if you care about having peace of mind.  The toilets were not stabled the best, and the sponge in our upgraded room was already used. Which, typically would bother us. However, giving what had transpired I figured I'll leave a thorough review. This was our first time here, and our first experience. This room mimic a room we had on our honeymoon, and so many things just took that experience away. It was unfortunate, and that's the only reason I'm writing this review. My wife tried to edit the same photo to give you all a better view of how big it truly was.we have a video, but unable to upload it as well. I will leave another room on Yelp, and Google and try to upload the videos as well.

name: The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection
description:
Located in Seattle, one mile from Pocket Beach, The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection provides accommodations with a fitness center, private parking, a terrace and a bar. This 4-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk, a business center and free WiFi. The property is 1,800 feet from the city center and a 10-minute walk from Space Needle.
The hotel will provide guests with air-conditioned rooms with a closet, a coffee machine, a fridge, a safety deposit box, a flat-screen TV and a private bathroom with a shower. At The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection all rooms are equipped with bed linen and towels.
Breakfast is available every morning, and includes à la carte, continental and American options. At the accommodation you'll find a restaurant serving American cuisine. Vegetarian, vegan and dairy-free options can also be requested.
Popular points of interest near The Sound Hotel Seattle Belltown, Tapestry Collection include Westlake Center, Museum of Pop Culture and Washington State Convention Center. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 1.2 miles from the hotel.

name: The Charter Hotel Seattle, Curio Collection By Hilton
description:
The Charter Hotel Seattle, Curio Collection By Hilton features air-conditioned rooms with cable flat-screen TV in the Seattle Central Business District district of Seattle. Among the various facilities of this property are a shared lounge and a bar. Guests can sample Argentinian and American dishes at the on-site restaurant.
At the hotel, rooms have a desk. The private bathroom is fitted with free toiletries. All guest rooms will provide guests with a fridge and coffee maker.
A continental or à la carte breakfast can be enjoyed at the property. Guests can enjoy The Fog Room, a rooftop lounge, at the property.
The property has a sauna.
A business center is at guests' disposal at Charter Seattle Curio Collection. Staff at the reception can provide information on what to do in the area.
Pike Place Market is 650 feet from the accommodations, while Space Needle is 0.7 mi from the property. Sea-Tac Airport is 12 mi away.

userReviews.title: Im großen und ganzen super! Würde das Hotel weiterempfehlen.
userReviews.positive:
Die Zimmer waren außergewöhnlich geräumig und modern/neu ausgestattet.
Das Hotel ist in sehr guter Lage und man kann Fußläufig alles erreichen.
Im EG befindet sich das Hauptrestaurant was aufgrund der Unruhen nur noch zum Frühstücken genutzt werden kann.
In der 16. Etage befindet sich the Fog eine sehr schöne Rooftop Bar die nun auch zum Abendessen genutzt werden kann.
Ich mag Seattle sehr und war schon öfter hier, leider ist es seitdem immer Krawalle stattfinden nicht mehr das gleiche. Sämtliche Geschäfte sind geschlossen, überall Polizei und wo man hinsieht Obdachlose und Drogenkonsum mitten am Tag.
Sehr Schade aber dafür kann das Hotel nichts.

name: Element Seattle Sea-Tac Airport
description:
Located in Seattle and with CenturyLink Field reachable within 12 miles, Element Seattle Sea-Tac Airport has concierge services, non-smoking rooms, a shared lounge, free WiFi and a terrace. Offering a restaurant, the property also has free bikes, as well as an indoor pool and a fitness center. The hotel features a hot tub and a 24-hour front desk.
At the hotel rooms contain air conditioning, a seating area, a flat-screen TV with cable channels, a kitchenette, a dining area and a private bathroom with a hairdryer and a bath or shower. At Element Seattle Sea-Tac Airport each room includes bed linen and towels.
Guests at the accommodation can enjoy a buffet or an American breakfast.
Element Seattle Sea-Tac Airport has a grill. The area is popular for cycling, and car rental is available at this 3-star hotel.
A business center and vending machines with snacks and drinks are available on site at the hotel.
Space Needle is 14 miles from Element Seattle Sea-Tac Airport, while Tiger Mountain State Forest is 19 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Seattle–Tacoma International Airport, 3.1 miles from the accommodation.

name: Warwick Seattle
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Warwick Seattle! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located just a 7 minutes' walk from the famous Pike Place Market, this 18-story hotel features an on-site restaurant. An indoor pool and whirlpool is also provided. A full continental breakfast is served daily.
Boasting unique accommodations inspired by Seattle culture, the spacious rooms of the Warwick Seattle feature private Juliet balconies and floor-to-ceiling windows. A refrigerator/mini-bar and coffee/tea makers are included.
Margaux at the Warwick provides an eclectic menu, simply described as Northwestern cuisine, combining ingredients and elements of Northwest-style cooking with local influences and accent in a casual atmosphere. Guests can enjoy breakfast, lunch, and dinner at the restaurant, also open for weekend brunch. The Margaux Lounge features a full-service bar and a lighter menu.
A 24-hour fitness centre is open to all guests, and features treadmills, an elliptical, a recumbent bicycle, free weights, and more. The business centre and weekday laundry services are also available.
The Warwick Seattle is 4 blocks from downtown Seattle. The Space Needle and Seattle Center are just 8 blocks away.

name: Hotel Andra Seattle MGallery Hotel Collection
description:
This luxury boutique hotel is in the heart of downtown Seattle located between the popular Belltown district and Lake Union. The hotel is within a 6 minutes' walk from famous Pike Place Market and Westlake Shopping Center. Hotel Ändra offers complimentary Wi-Fi.
All rooms at Hotel Ändra feature subtle Scandinavian decor and include a 37" flat-screen TV, clock radio with Bluetooth pairing capabilities, ironing facilities, a private bar with premium spirits and a coffee maker. The bathrooms include plush spa bathrobes, luxury bath amenities and a hairdryer.
Hotel Ändra features Lola Restaurant, which serves Greek and Pacific Northwest cuisine. Assaggio Ristorante features authentic Northern Italian cuisine. Both restaurants offer room service.
Guests can work out in the on-site fitness center or take advantage of the hotel's discounts to nearby fitness clubs.
Hotel Ändra is a 15-minute walk from The Seattle Center and Space Needle. SeaTac International Airport is 15 mi from the hotel.

name: Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle Downtown Convention Center
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle Downtown Convention Center! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located conveniently in the center of Seattle, Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle Downtown Convention Center offers air-conditioned rooms, a fitness center, free WiFi and a bar. This 3-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk and an ATM. Private parking is available on site.
At the hotel, all rooms are equipped with a desk, a flat-screen TV, a private bathroom, bed linen and towels. The units feature a wardrobe.
A buffet breakfast is available every morning at Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle Downtown Convention Center.
The accommodations offers a terrace.
Popular points of interest near Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle Downtown Convention Center include Pike Place Market, Space Needle and Seattle Center. The nearest airport is Boeing Field/King County International Airport, 7.5 mi from the hotel.

name: Hyatt at Olive 8
description:
Featuring an indoor swimming pool with a city view and plush lounge chairs, this modern Seattle hotel is 10 minutes’ drive from the University of Washington. A full-service spa is also featured.
Styled in a soothing color scheme, each modern room provides an iPod docking station, a flat-screen cable TV and a sitting area. LEED Certified fixtures and amenities are featured in all rooms at Hyatt at Olive 8.
After a day in downtown Seattle, guests can enjoy a sauna and a fitness center at Olive 8 Hyatt. A 24-hour front desk is offered. Free Wi-Fi access is available throughout the hotel.
Guests can enjoy coffee and lite bites at Urbane Market on site. Urbane, the on-site restaurant, features a farm-to-table dining experience from produce of the Northwest.
Pike Place Fish Market and the Space Needle are within a 20 minutes’ walk of Hyatt at Olive 8. Seattle-Tacoma International Airport is 20 minutes’ drive from Hyatt at Olive 8.

name: Kimpton Palladian Hotel, an IHG Hotel
description:
Offering a restaurant on-site, Kimpton Palladian Hotel is located in Seattle. Guest rooms feature pop-art pillows while certain units have a claw footed bathtub. The hotel is 1,000 feet from Pike Place Market and 0.6 mi from the Space Needle.
Each air-conditioned room here will provide you with a satellite TV with pay-per-view channels.TV, an iPod docking station and a mini-bar. Featuring a bathrobe and free Bigelow bath amenities, the private bathrooms come with a hairdryer.
An evening wine hour is held every night from 17:00 to 18:00 at Kimpton Palladian Hotel. Free bikes are also available. Other facilities offered at the property include meeting facilities, luggage storage and dry cleaning.
Guests can enjoy bold flavors at the hotel’s seafood restaurant, Shaker + Spear.
Sea-Tac Airport is 12 mi away. The Washington State Convention Center as well as the Seattle’s waterfront can be reached within 12 minutes' walk. Safeco Field is 1.9 mi from the Kimpton Palladian Hotel.

address.full: 2000 Second Avenue, Belltown, Seattle, WA 98121, United States of America
