name: Courtyard by Marriott Seattle Northgate
description:
Located in Seattle, 7.3 miles from Space Needle, Courtyard by Marriott Seattle Northgate has accommodations with free bikes, private parking, a fitness center and a shared lounge. With free WiFi, this 3-star hotel has a terrace and a bar. The property provides room service, a 24-hour front desk and luggage storage for guests.
All rooms come with air conditioning, a flat-screen TV with satellite channels, a fridge, a coffee machine, a shower, free toiletries and a desk. The rooms have a private bathroom, a hairdryer and bed linen.
The hotel offers a à la carte or American breakfast. At Courtyard by Marriott Seattle Northgate you'll find a restaurant serving American cuisine. Vegetarian and gluten-free options can also be requested.
The area is popular for hiking and cycling, and car rental is available at this 3-star hotel.
There's an in-house snack bar and guests can also use the business area.
CenturyLink Field is 8.4 miles from the accommodation, while Tiger Mountain State Forest is 24 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Seattle Lake Union Seaplane Base Airport, 6.8 miles from Courtyard by Marriott Seattle Northgate.

userReviews.title: Not too bad
userReviews.positive: My stay at the Marriott was overall okay. I have stayed at other Marriott hotels and had better service. The facility was clean and I did enjoy that they had a bistro to order from for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Although the options were limited they still had a good variety to choose from. Room was clean and a good size to accommodate my family of 3, with a King size bed and pull out in the sofa (really comfy). Parking was conveniently located on lower level level of garage. The cost was a bit pricey but worth it, although there is street parking located nearby, but you have to walk about a good 5 mins to get to the hotel. There was a gas station and 7-eleven located within walking distance of about 2-5minutes, and also there is a Mediterranean restaurant within a 10minutes walk. Room includes microwave and fridge (which only holds very small items).
userReviews.negative: The only thing I did not like about my stay is that trash pick up was not offered in addition to receiving room clean service. Our stay was 5 days , so you can imagine the pile up of trash and also we needed to change out towel. I had called the receptionist and spoke with a man in the morning (unsure of his name), and with a snarky attitude told me that services are not being offered due to short of staff, and I had asked him what the policy states for cleaning when the stay is longer than 3 days. He replied with "the only thing we can offer you is more towels." I was displeased be cause I've stayed at other Marriott hotels that were the same size and same amount of staff and was offered these services after 3 day stays.  Needless to say I dont think I would return to this Marriott, if I were to visit again, just based off the receptionist.
userReviews.room: King Room with Sofa Bed - Non-Smoking

We almost considered changing due to the crummy mattress, but the location fits our needs very well.

name: Hotel Nexus; BW Signature Collection
description:
Hotel Nexus; BW Signature Collection offers a convenient location only moments from the Northgate Mall shopping center. Guests at the hotel can also easily visit the University of Washington along with delicious restaurants, shopping centers and entertainment options.
Easily accessible from Interstate 5 and 10 minutes' drive from central Seattle, this modern hotel provides comfortable accommodations along with free Wi-Fi and free parking. A local area shuttle service with three route schedules (the city center, University district, and Northgate) is offered three times daily.
Guests at the Hotel Nexus; BW Signature Collection can start the day with a free hot breakfast buffet or take advantage of in-room microwaves and refrigerators. The hotel also features an on-site fitness center with state-of-the-art Precor equipment, as well as modern business facilities.The seasonal outdoor pool is open from Memorial day until Labor Day.
The completely nonsmoking Hotel Nexus; BW Signature Collection also features an on-site restaurant, Saffron Bar and Grill, which services a variety of American, Indian and Mediterranean cuisine.

Space Needle is 5.6 mi from Hampton Inn Seattle/Northgate, while Pike Place Market is 6.2 mi away. The nearest airport is Sea-Tac Airport, 17 mi from Hampton Inn & Suites by Hilton Seattle/Northgate.

userReviews.title: Stressful
userReviews.positive: Nice accommodations. Staff had to heard back from home office which they never received. See below.
userReviews.negative: When I showd up on the 28th of Sept. I found I had made a mistake. I made the reservations for the 28th of Aug rather than the 28th of Sept.  This was on Booking .com conf. # 8514713  pin 1788. I was on the phone with Booking.com for over two hours trying to resolve the problem. They contacted Hampton to try to resolve, but Hampton, as I am told, would not respond to them. The result was I paid over $900.00 for a room in Aug and then another $600.00 in Sept. Booking.com was trying to get Hampton to honor the original booking but again my mistake but you got your money. And speaking of making a mistake. When I registered for the room, I specially asked for 3 nights. I remember this because I held up three fingers as I was saying it. Do you know what it is like to come back to hotel and find out that all your belongings have been taking out and stored because someone punched in 2 rather 3 nights. I guess Hampton is not immune to mistakes. I guess you can figure out that this left me with a lasting impression that when it is convenient you will work with a traveler. Not in this case.

name: Hotel Ballard
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Hotel Ballard! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located in a brand new building in historic Ballard, this boutique hotel features views of the Olympic Mountains from a furnished rooftop terrace. Premium linens are included in each guest rooms.
Free Wi-Fi and a flat-screen cable TV with extended channels are standard in each guest room and suite at Hotel Ballard. Plush bathrobes, slippers and a hairdryer are provided in the private bathroom. A spacious work desk and coffee-making facilities are included.
The Stoneburner restaurant and bar, located in the hotel lobby, offers small-plate cuisine. Room service is available and features a breakfast menu from 07:00 to 11:00. Complimentary fruit and pastries are offered in the lobby at 07:00.
24-hour concierge service is offered. Underground parking is available. Guests of Hotel Ballard receive free access to fitness classes, saunas, hot tubs and 2 lap pools at the 24-hour Olympic Athletic Club.
Discovery Park is 3 miles away. Pike Place Market is 5 miles away. Seattle-Tacoma International Airport (Sea-Tac) is 30 minutes’ drive away.

name: Ballard Inn
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Ballard Inn! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Just 5.5 miles from downtown Seattle, this historic Washington hotel offers charming accommodations with free Wi-Fi. Pike's Place market is less than a 15 minute drive away.
Comfortably furnished, each room at the Ballard Inn includes a flat-screen TV with cable. All bright rooms feature Victorian inspired art and fixtures.
At Inn Ballard, guests can relax in the lobby complete with plush sofas and large picture windows overlooking the neighborhood. A 24-hour front desk is available for added convenience.
Offering panoramic views of Puget Sound and the Olympic Mountains, the Golden Gardens Park is 3 miles from Ballard Inn.

userReviews.title: Budget Luxury with Shared Bathrooms Exists
userReviews.positive: Wow!  What a classy place. Let's just say I never would have associated a sense of luxury with any place that indicated that it also had "shared bathrooms."  Well, the Ballard Inn shows how you can be classy while offering shared bathrooms that are kept exceptionally clean.  I felt as though I had the Inn to myself and could only tell others were there by the used towels in the clearly marked collection bin in the bathroom.  The decor is tasteful and well executed and the rooms are well appointed and comfortable.  Overall an unexpected  high quality stay for a budget price.
userReviews.negative: I have no complaints.  It is clear that Management clearly pays attention to the finer details and that even at a budget price, customer service is a priority.

userReviews.title: Cute Hotel in a great area
userReviews.positive: Loved the location and feel of this property. The hotel sits right on Ballard with a plethora of restaurants and shops right outside the door. It’s also home to a Sunday farmers market that was a blast to walk through. Striking distance to the locks and many other places, especially with a electric bike/scooter. Staff was very friendly and they take cleanliness seriously. This property is residence-hall-style where guests share a bathroom. The staff was on top of cleaning and seemed like they were checking on the bathrooms almost every hour or so. I never once went into a mess.  The area can be a little noisy, but ear plugs are provided. They did not refill water bottles with room cleaning and I found the electric outlets to be troublesome (not enough power and then not able to withstand the pad charger types. Overheats), but I made them aware of the issue and it could have only been that room. Overall great place to stay if you’re looking to get out and about and not stick to your hotel room. They provide the comfortable, decent quality necessities and they do it well, but that’s about what you can expect.

name: Embassy Suites By Hilton Seattle Downtown Pioneer Square
description:
Set in the Pioneer Square district of Seattle, 1,000 feet from CenturyLink Field, Embassy Suites By Hilton Seattle Downtown Pioneer Square features a complimentary evening reception and an on-site bar. The property is located 0.9 mi from Pike Place Market, 1.7 mi from the Space Needle and 1.9 mi from the Seattle Center. Local points of interest like Safeco Field and Columbia Center are reachable within 2,300 feet and 2297 feet, respectively.
All guest rooms in the hotel are fitted with a flat-screen TV with satellite channels. Embassy Suites Seattle Downtown features certain units that include city views, and all rooms have a private bathroom and a desk. Guest rooms at the accommodations come with a seating area.
An American breakfast is served every morning at the property. The on-site restaurant, 13 Coins, offers a 24-hour menu with a variety of breakfast, lunch, and dinner options.
Staff at Embassy Suites By Hilton Seattle Downtown Pioneer Square are always available to provide information at the reception. A swimming pool and fitness center are also available at the property.
Seattle Great Wheel is a 14-minute walk from the hotel. The nearest airport is Sea-Tac Airport, 11 mi from the property.

address.full: 255 South King Street, Pioneer Square, Seattle, WA 98104, United States of America

name: Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle University District
description:
Located in Seattle’s University District just 3.7 mi from the city center, this hotel features modern and colorful guest rooms each with a fully equipped kitchen. A complimentary breakfast and an indoor pool are featured at Residence Inn by Marriott Seattle University District.
The air-conditioned guest rooms here include free WiFi access, a seating area with a sofa, and a flat-screen TV. A dishwasher, microwave, and a private bathroom with free toiletries are also offered.
A mini-market, launderette, and fitness center can all be found on site at Seattle University District Residence Inn by Marriott. A business center and a 24-hour front desk are also available.
The Burke Museum of Natural History and Culture is just a 4-minute walk from the hotel and Woodland Park Zoo is less than a 10-minute drive. Seattle-Tacoma International Airport is located 18 mi away.
